    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3620834529" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3620834529" />
    <a title="Bill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106293767-bill"><img alt="Bill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576529794p2/106293767.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3620834529?book_show_action=true">Nov 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bill" href="/user/show/106293767-bill">Bill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=read-in-2020">read-in-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=religion">religion</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=4-star">4-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=rtc-2020">rtc-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106293767-bill?shelf=turkey">turkey</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3620834529" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7822028794000015865">Ella Rubenstein keeps busy enough cooking and caring for her husband and children and their big Victorian house in Northampton, Massachusetts, that she can mostly ignore her anger at her husband&apos;s infidelities and her sense of loss at the children&apos;s lessening need for her as they focus on high school and college. Chance provides her an opportunity to rekindle her own college-age passion for literature as a reader for a Boston publishing house.<br/><br/>We read her first assignment, <i>Sweet Blasphemy</i>, by A. </span>
  <span id="freeText7822028794000015865" style="display:none">Ella Rubenstein keeps busy enough cooking and caring for her husband and children and their big Victorian house in Northampton, Massachusetts, that she can mostly ignore her anger at her husband's infidelities and her sense of loss at the children's lessening need for her as they focus on high school and college. Chance provides her an opportunity to rekindle her own college-age passion for literature as a reader for a Boston publishing house.<br /><br />We read her first assignment, <i>Sweet Blasphemy</i>, by A. Z. Zahara of Holland, along with her, and learn the story of the intense friendship of the Sufi dervish Shams of Tabriz and the Islamic scholar Rumi, in thirteenth-century Turkey. Reading the manuscript inspires Ella to connect with its author via the Internet, a step that takes her life into a whole new direction, just as Rumi's experience with Shams transforms him into a great mystic and poet.<br /><br />The fictionalized account of the real-life Rumi and Shams is stronger than the contemporary branch of this dual timeline novel, and I would have liked a more interesting denouement, but I enjoyed the novel and learned a lot about a place and time with which I was unfamiliar.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7822028794000015865" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

