<div id="review_3707191292" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3707191292" />
    <a title="Tanu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/114780411-tanu"><img alt="Tanu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643309480p2/114780411.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3707191292?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tanu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tanu" href="/user/show/114780411-tanu">Tanu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=self-help">self-help</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=5-stars">5-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=psychology">psychology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114780411-tanu?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3707191292" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16122197596061672235"><i> <b> &quot;Love cannot be explained. It can only be experienced. Love cannot be explained, yet it explains all. &quot;</b></i> <br/><i><br/>This novel, like love, must be experienced rather than merely read.<br/></i><br/>The Forty Rules of Love is a charming mash-up of two stories, one set in modern times with Ella, a proofreader in a literary agency, as the protagonist, and the other set in the 13th century (the story of the greatest poet of all time Rumi and Shams of Tabriz).<br/><b><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6542440.Elif_Shafak' title='Elif Shafak' rel='nofollow noopener'>Elif Shafak</a> nailed it in narrating Rumi&apos;s and Sham&apos;s story the way</b></span>
  <span id="freeText16122197596061672235" style="display:none"><i> <b> "Love cannot be explained. It can only be experienced. Love cannot be explained, yet it explains all. "</b></i> <br /><i><br />This novel, like love, must be experienced rather than merely read.<br /></i><br />The Forty Rules of Love is a charming mash-up of two stories, one set in modern times with Ella, a proofreader in a literary agency, as the protagonist, and the other set in the 13th century (the story of the greatest poet of all time Rumi and Shams of Tabriz).<br /><b><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6542440.Elif_Shafak" title="Elif Shafak" rel="nofollow noopener">Elif Shafak</a> nailed it in narrating Rumi's and Sham's story the way it was shown from many perspectives sometimes from the perspective of Shams, sometimes a beggar, sometimes zealot or Rumi or prostitute or even the family of Rumi. But the narrative of Ella lacks multiple perspectives. It is just from the perspective of Ella, if it was from the point of view of Aziz or her children or even her husband then I would have loved it even more. I had no idea about Sufism which I got to know through the book. Sufism, although, it sounds religious it is way beyond it. It is a pure way of living. </b><br /><i><br />It usually takes me 5-7 days to finish a book. However, this took far too long. Is this book tiring and boring? ABSOLUTELY NOT. The narrative is so intriguing that at no point one feels bored. I took this long for I found myself not just reading but devouring the enchanted words not just into my mind but into my soul. Yes, it is that good. You will need some time to sink it in.</i><br /><b><br />Not everyone is going to like or rather understand this book. But hey, “If you only read the books that everyone else is reading, you can only think what everyone else is thinking.” – <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3354.Haruki_Murakami" title="Haruki Murakami" rel="nofollow noopener">Haruki Murakami</a><br /></b><br />I suggest picking this book only if you are ready to challenge and transform your beliefs about love in the highest spiritual way.<br /><b> <i><br />Fun fact: Every chapter of the book starts with the letter B. </i></b> </span>
  <a data-text-id="16122197596061672235" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


